fields.text:
Qualified by 4 years as technical advisor and 7 years of post-MSc academic experience in solar
energy research. Expertise in data acquisition, data analysis and modeling including statistical
analysis and machine learning. Programming skills: HTML/Javascript, Django, Python, MATLAB, R, Java, LabVIEW, SQL, MDX, UNIX shell.

Business Intelligence: diagnose complex data and modeling problems, analyze technical issues, recommend solutions

Machine learning in MATLAB and Python (scikit-learn): linear and logistic regression, clustering, dimensionality reduction, anomaly detection. Familiar with support vector machines and recommendation systems
Statistical analysis and advanced regression techniques, signal processing, model fitting. Background in data mining and algorithm development
Experience with large-scale code bases, desire to dive in, understand existing code

Teamwork and management responsibilities: ability to supervise and work well with others in diverse work settings. Launched and supported several research projects allowing my teams to produce data quicker and publish first on several topics

Communication skills: broad experience in both written (6 scientific publications, periodic reports) and oral (16 presentations at international conferences, group meetings, communication with non-specialist audiences) scientific communication

Mentoring and teaching: responsible for the daily supervision of BSc and MSc students, who completed their projects on time and to a high standards. Two years teaching assistant in the MATLAB/LabVIEW course “Applied Informatics for Medical Students”
